Title: Geometry, Isometries and Gauging of (2,1) Heterotic Sigma-Models
Authors: M. Abou Zeid and C. M. Hull
Comments: 12 pages, LaTeX, no figures. Minor changes; version to appear in
  Physics Letters B
Report-no: QMW-PH-96-29
Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B398 (1997) 291-297
\\
  The geometry of (2,1) supersymmetric sigma-models is reviewed and the
conditions under which they have isometry symmetries are analysed. Certain
potentials are constructed that play an important role in the gauging of such
symmetries. The gauged action is found for a special class of models.
